WorkItem.Description:
Hi, consider the two classes below in TS 0.9 Beta:

```JavaScript
class Foo {
    constructor() {
        var x = 10;
    }
}

class Bar {
    constructor(
        ) {
            var x = 10;
    }
}
```

The only difference is that in Bar the parenthesis following the constructor is spread over two lines.

This causes the `var x` statement to have an extra indent - __as it is typed out__. 

Hitting Control+K, Control+D (format document) reduces the indent to the correct amount.

However, editing `var x =  10` by deleting the closing semicolon and then typing that semicolon again causes `var x = 10` to leap to the right.

All this jumping around is driving my cat crazy! 

(this bug was introduced in 0.9 I believe)

